description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join the expanding procurement team at Wirral Community Health &amp; Care NHS Foundation Trust following the creation of a new post. The team is currently based in Albert Lodge on the Victoria Central Hospital site and works closely with clinical and corporate colleagues across all of the trust sites both in Wirral and East Cheshire. We achieved Level 1 accreditation against NHS Standards for Procurement last year and are currently working towards Level 2 accreditation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will provide an efficient and professional client focused stock distribution service, effectively delivering, handling and managing trust stock, dealing with enquiries and requests in a polite and timely manner. In addition to this the new post holder will provide stock management and procurement data to evidence efficient stock control; scoping, development and implementation of a trust wide materials management service(s) to new areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLEASE NOTE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In order to be considered for this role please provide the information below in the supporting information section of your application (failure to do so may result in your application not being considered) :-&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please specify the vehicle categories for which you hold a licence from the following list: Motorbike (A), Car (B), Car with Trailer (B+E), Medium Sized Vehicle (C1), Medium Sized Vehicle (C1+E), Minibus (D1), Minibus with Trailer (D1+E), Large Goods Vehicle (C), Large Good Vehicle with Trailer (C+E), Passenger Carrying Vehicle (D), Passenger Carrying Vehicle (D+E) or C1 Provisional Licence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How many penalty points do you currently have on your driving licence?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you have penalty points, please state the Endorsement Offence Codes and the date of issue&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working hours for this role are 7am to 3pm Monday to Friday as part of the role will involve receiving deliveries of PPE stock up to 5 days per week. There may be a need for some flexibility to receive later deliveries on occasion, this would be on a rota basis and within the 37.5. weekly hours.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Using knowledge and/or experience of manual handling the ability to move and deliver stock to sites across Wirral and East Cheshire, transporting stock in a transit van, is an essential element of the role.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While prior experience in the public sector and knowledge of stock management are highly desirable a strong customer service ethos and ability to problem solve and work co-operatively with others to meet the team’s targets are also important.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Heather Thornton&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Senior Contract Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: heather.thornton5@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0151 514 2888&lt;/p&gt;
